    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cell-Phone Cars For the L.I.R.R.?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>State University of New York Prof E Ann Kaplan letter on September 10 article suggests Long Island Rail Road ban cell phones in all but a few cars (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Re cell phones on Long Island Rail Road trains [''Cell Phone Abuse Is Riding the Rails,'' Sept. 10]: there's a solution that I learned about while travelling this summer in England, where trains have designated ''quiet coaches,'' in which cell phones are banned. How about having one or two ''cell phone carriages'' on each L.I.R.R. train, and banning cell phone use on the rest? Let them enjoy one another's company, leaving the rest of us to peace and quiet.</p>
        <p>(Prof.) E. ANN KAPLAN  SUNY-Stony Brook</p>
      </block>
